      • getHighestNode

        public Node getHighestNode()
        Returns:
        The node in this instance's model with the highest degree, which is not yet filled in. This node is REMOVED from the queue!

      • removeNode

        public boolean removeNode(Node key)
        Removes a node from the instance. This does not add the node to the queue with unfilled positions in the model.

      • putInQueue

        public void putInQueue(Node n)
        Add a node to the queue of unfilled positions. In order to succeed, the model of this graph must contain the graphlet, while the instance itself does not.
        Parameters:
        n - The node to be added.

      • isComplete

        public boolean isComplete()
        Checks whether this graphlet is complete. A graphlet is complete if all of its nodes are filled in.
        Returns:
        true if the graphlet is complete, false if it is not.

      • getCompatibleNodes

        public java.util.Set<Node> getCompatibleNodes(Node key,
                                     Graph g)
        Seeks the nodes in the graph that can be placed at the specified position within this graphlet, given the current status of this GraphletInstance.
        Parameters:
        key - The position for which compatible nodes are searched.
        g - The graph in which the nodes are searched.
        Returns:
        A set containing the compatible nodes.

        Calculates the intersection between a number of sets, i.e. the set containing the nodes present in all sets.
        Parameters:
        sets - A set containing the sets to be intersected.
        Returns:

      • verschil

        public static java.util.Set<Node> verschil(java.util.Set<Node> geheel,
                           java.util.Collection<Node> deel)
        Calculates the difference between two sets, i.e. the set containing the nodes present in one set, but not in the other.
        Parameters:
        geheel - The set containing the nodes which must be kept.
        deel - The set whose nodes must be removed from the first set.
        Returns:
        The set containing the nodes in the first set, but not the second.
